{"data":{"markdown":{"html":"<p>Computational Biology, Systems Biology, Genome-Scale Metabolic Modeling, Microbiome, Machine Learning.</p>\n<p>Dr. Bernstein is an Assistant Professor in Electrical and Biomedical Engineering with a secondary appointment in Microbiology and Molecular Genetics. He earned his BS in Mechanical Engineering from the University of Vermont and PhD in Biomedical Engineering from Boston University. Prior to joining UVM, he was a postdoctoral researcher at the University of California, Berkeley. His research in the field of systems biology combines bioinformatics, computational modeling, and machine learning to gain quantitative understanding of microbial ecosystems. His work is at the forefront of genome-scale metabolic modeling where he has published in leading journals and presented at international conferences. Applications of his work focus on understanding the role of microbial organisms in environmental and human health.</p>","frontmatter":{"image":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/b3439c85868919652f4c53b138c095c1/f99e8/dbernstein.png","srcSet":"/static/b3439c85868919652f4c53b138c095c1/2bc09/dbernstein.png 88w,\n/static/b3439c85868919652f4c53b138c095c1/a527b/dbernstein.png 175w,\n/static/b3439c85868919652f4c53b138c095c1/f99e8/dbernstein.png 350w,\n/static/b3439c85868919652f4c53b138c095c1/7932e/dbernstein.png 700w","sizes":"(min-width: 350px) 350px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/b3439c85868919652f4c53b138c095c1/ca93e/dbernstein.webp 88w,\n/static/b3439c85868919652f4c53b138c095c1/746e2/dbernstein.webp 175w,\n/static/b3439c85868919652f4c53b138c095c1/b0882/dbernstein.webp 350w,\n/static/b3439c85868919652f4c53b138c095c1/2cafc/dbernstein.webp 700w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 350px) 350px, 100vw"}]},"width":350,"height":350}}},"title":"About David Bernstein"}}}}